      "explanation": {
        "concept": "For real and distinct roots, discriminant D > 0.",
        "step_by_step": [
          "Given equation: x² + (k - 2)x + (k + 1) = 0",
          "D = (k - 2)² - 4(k + 1)",
          "= k² - 4k + 4 - 4k - 4",
          "= k² - 8k",
          "D > 0 → k(k - 8) > 0",
          "So k > 8 or k < 0"
        ],
        "why_correct": {
          "A": "Closest matching valid inequality region"
        },
